Package prkmodel.types

Interface Microglia

All Superinterfaces:
NervousSystemElement
All Known Implementing Classes:
DefaultMicroglia, RepastMicroglia
public interface Microglia extends NervousSystemElement
Interface representing a microglia in the nervous system. Microglia are a type of glial cell located throughout the brain and spinal cord that act as the main form of active immune defense in the central nervous system.

This interface defines the behavior of microglia, including cytokines production.
